    "subtopic": "Example 3.14",
    "difficulty": "Hard",
    "type": "ProblemSolving",
    "question": "Box: 3 blue, 2 red, 3 green pens. Select 2 at random. X=blue count, Y=red count. Find joint f(x,y) and P((X,Y)∈A) where A={(x,y): x+y≤1}.",
    "correctAnswer": "0.5357",
    "hints": [
      "Hypergeometric for each (x,y) with x+y≤2.",
      "Total ways C(8,2)=28."
    ],
    "solution": {
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 1,
          "title": "Joint PMF",
          "content": "f(x,y)=C(3,x)C(2,y)C(3,2-x-y)/C(8,2) for valid x,y",
          "explanation": "Multivariate hypergeometric."
        },
        {
          "step": 2,
          "title": "Region A",
          "content": "Sum f(0,0)+f(1,0)+f(0,1) = 3/28+6/28+6/28 = 15/28 ≈ 0.536",
          "explanation": "At most one colored pen in blue+red sense."
        }
      ],
      "finalAnswer": "≈0.536",
      "commonMistakes": []
    },
    "tags": [
      "important",
      "exam-style"
    ]
  },
